1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:03,268
Julia:
<i>Chester's mill is a place</i>
<i>like any other.</i>

2
00:00:03,270 --> 00:00:05,270
<i>At least it used to be</i>

3
00:00:05,272 --> 00:00:07,272
<i>Until we were cut off</i>
<i>from the rest of the world</i>

4
00:00:07,274 --> 00:00:09,174
<i>By a mysterious dome.</i>

5
00:00:12,780 --> 00:00:15,514
<i>Invisible, indestructible,</i>

6
00:00:15,516 --> 00:00:18,050
<i>Inescapable.</i>

7
00:00:18,052 --> 00:00:20,052
We're trapped.

8
00:00:20,054 --> 00:00:22,588
Julia:
<i>We don't know where it</i>
<i>came from or why it's here,</i>

9
00:00:22,590 --> 00:00:25,024
<i>But now that we're all trapped</i>
<i>under the dome together,</i>

10
00:00:25,026 --> 00:00:28,627
<i>None of our secrets are safe.</i>

11
00:00:28,629 --> 00:00:29,695
Barbie:
<i>I linked up with a bookie.</i>

12
00:00:29,697 --> 00:00:31,630
Taking bets?

13
00:00:31,632 --> 00:00:34,233
Making sure that people paid
what they owed.

14
00:00:34,235 --> 00:00:35,701
When I get home,
you better be gone.

15
00:00:35,703 --> 00:00:36,702
Big jim:
<i>You ever consider</i>

16
00:00:36,704 --> 00:00:38,704
A career in law enforcement?

17
00:00:40,306 --> 00:00:41,373
Both:
The pink stars are falling.

18
00:00:42,108 --> 00:00:44,410
Shh...

19
00:00:50,216 --> 00:00:51,583
norrie?

20
00:00:51,585 --> 00:00:53,485
Norrie, where are you?

21
00:00:53,487 --> 00:00:55,821
Right behind you, genius.

22
00:00:55,823 --> 00:00:58,057
I didn't realize that
crashing with a farm kid

23
00:00:58,059 --> 00:01:00,092
Meant that I had to get up
at the ass-crack of dawn.

24
00:01:00,094 --> 00:01:01,794
Come on,
it's about the dome.

25
00:01:01,796 --> 00:01:03,162
Really? Is it gone?

26
00:01:03,164 --> 00:01:04,296
Are we finally free?

27
00:01:04,298 --> 00:01:05,464
You'll see.

28
00:01:05,466 --> 00:01:07,199
I've been thinking
about our seizures.

29
00:01:07,201 --> 00:01:08,634
About what we said.

30
00:01:08,636 --> 00:01:10,235
"the pink stars
are falling."

31
00:01:10,237 --> 00:01:13,472
Not yet, but if the dome
is really sending out messages,

32
00:01:13,474 --> 00:01:15,674
Then we're
like human receivers.

33
00:01:15,676 --> 00:01:17,776
We can catch a few of the
transmissions on our own,

34
00:01:17,778 --> 00:01:19,645
But when we get
too close to each other...

35
00:01:21,582 --> 00:01:23,148
Feedback.

36
00:01:24,217 --> 00:01:26,118
Joe, why would the dome
only talk to us?

37
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:27,286
I don't know.

38
00:01:27,288 --> 00:01:29,555
But when I came out here
to find out,

39
00:01:29,557 --> 00:01:31,190
I saw this.

40
00:01:36,129 --> 00:01:37,663
Yeah, right?

41
00:01:37,665 --> 00:01:41,100
Monarch butterflies
aren't even in season.

42
00:01:41,102 --> 00:01:42,768
They shouldn't be anywhere
near chester's mill

43
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:44,336
This time of year.

44
00:01:44,338 --> 00:01:46,538
Maybe the dome sent them.

45
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:50,542
Maybe it's trying to tell us
that the dome's just a cocoon,

46
00:01:50,544 --> 00:01:52,544
And when it finally goes away,

47
00:01:52,546 --> 00:01:54,313
We'll all get to be
something new.

48
00:01:54,315 --> 00:01:56,815
You realize most caterpillars
are actually eaten

49
00:01:56,817 --> 00:01:58,484
Before they turn
into butterflies?

50
00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:20,706
Mr. Rennie.

51
00:02:20,708 --> 00:02:23,242
Oh, thank god.

52
00:02:23,244 --> 00:02:25,177
What took you so long?

53
00:02:25,179 --> 00:02:27,546
Feeling better
there, darling?

54
00:02:27,548 --> 00:02:30,549
Better?
I've been down here all night.

55
00:02:30,551 --> 00:02:33,685
Why haven't you gotten
the police yet?

56
00:02:33,687 --> 00:02:36,622
Mr. Rennie,

57
00:02:36,624 --> 00:02:38,857
You're gonna get me
out of here, right?

58
00:02:38,859 --> 00:02:41,460
Of course.

59
00:02:41,462 --> 00:02:43,395
Soon as you tell me
exactly what it is

60
00:02:43,397 --> 00:02:44,663
You're doing down here.

61
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:49,268
He's been keeping me prisoner!

62
00:02:50,403 --> 00:02:51,403
Who?

63
00:02:51,405 --> 00:02:53,705
Your son.

64
00:02:53,707 --> 00:02:55,541
Junior?

65
00:02:55,543 --> 00:02:58,610
No. Why would...
Why would...?

66
00:02:58,612 --> 00:03:00,646
Why would he do
something like that?

67
00:03:00,648 --> 00:03:02,814
Because he's insane.

68
00:03:02,816 --> 00:03:07,953
You got to get me out of here
before he comes back.

69
00:03:10,324 --> 00:03:12,191
Big jim?

70
00:03:12,193 --> 00:03:14,226
Please, please!

71
00:03:14,228 --> 00:03:16,195
I just, uh, I just need to
think on this a little bit.

72
00:03:16,197 --> 00:03:17,196
No, no, no!

73
00:03:17,198 --> 00:03:18,630
You can't leave me down here!

74
00:03:18,632 --> 00:03:19,765
You can't... You...

75
00:03:19,767 --> 00:03:22,301
No, wait! Wait! Help!

76
00:03:22,303 --> 00:03:23,769
Please! No! Help!

77
00:03:23,771 --> 00:03:25,437
Help!

78
00:03:25,439 --> 00:03:27,773
Help! No!

79
00:03:38,518 --> 00:03:39,518
Damn it, coggins,
I thought we were done.

80
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,752
What are you doing here?
Jim.

81
00:03:40,754 --> 00:03:43,388
I received a very
troubling message.

82
00:03:43,390 --> 00:03:44,923
No! I have to tell you.

83
00:03:44,925 --> 00:03:46,525
What message?

84
00:03:46,527 --> 00:03:48,493
From the lord almighty.

85
00:03:48,495 --> 00:03:50,262
He whispered
one word to me.

86
00:03:50,264 --> 00:03:51,930
Moab.

87
00:03:51,932 --> 00:03:52,998
Moab?

88
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,467
Moab.

89
00:03:55,469 --> 00:03:58,270
You better check the batteries
in your hearing aid, coggins,

90
00:03:58,272 --> 00:03:59,905
'cause that's not even a word.

91
00:03:59,907 --> 00:04:02,975
Jim! Moab was a place.

92
00:04:02,977 --> 00:04:04,676
A very wicked place.

93
00:04:04,678 --> 00:04:06,878
Much like chester's mill.

94
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,447
I'm warning you, reverend.

95
00:04:08,449 --> 00:04:11,016
Stay away from me.

96
00:04:11,018 --> 00:04:12,484
Jim.

97
00:04:14,988 --> 00:04:16,855
Ji...

98
00:04:18,826 --> 00:04:20,892
Deep, distorted voice:
Moab.

99
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:26,798
moab.

100
00:04:28,669 --> 00:04:32,004
Moab... Moab.

101
00:04:33,841 --> 00:04:37,476
Moab.

102
00:04:40,046 --> 00:04:41,713
Joe:
Over here.

103
00:04:41,715 --> 00:04:44,916
Norrie:
Look at them all.

104
00:04:44,918 --> 00:04:47,486
Oh, my god, there's more.

105
00:04:48,888 --> 00:04:50,489
Where did they all come from?

106
00:04:50,491 --> 00:04:52,557
So beautiful.

107
00:04:55,595 --> 00:04:56,728
Barbie?

108
00:04:56,730 --> 00:04:58,764
What is this?

109
00:04:58,766 --> 00:05:00,632
Isn't it amazing?

110
00:05:17,717 --> 00:05:19,484
Huh.

111
00:05:19,486 --> 00:05:23,422
These guys are suddenly
paying attention to us?

112
00:05:23,424 --> 00:05:24,623
Look.

113
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:27,092
They're bussing in
more soldiers?

114
00:05:27,094 --> 00:05:29,928
No, civilians.

115
00:05:31,664 --> 00:05:33,632
Hey, that's frank!

116
00:05:33,634 --> 00:05:35,701
Norrie: Who?
Joe: My cousin.

117
00:05:35,703 --> 00:05:37,703
He went away to college
before the dome came down.

118
00:05:41,541 --> 00:05:43,542
Okay, it's been over a week
since this thing came down.

119
00:05:43,544 --> 00:05:45,610
Military hasn't let
anybody near here.

120
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:50,749
So why bus
the families in now?

121
00:05:50,751 --> 00:05:53,385
Haven't you ever been to camp?

122
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:57,489
They're finally giving us
our own visitors' day.

123
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:20,545
Julia:
<i>We have official confirmation</i>

124
00:06:20,547 --> 00:06:23,148
From military representatives

125
00:06:23,150 --> 00:06:24,783
That at 10:00 a.M. This morning,

126
00:06:24,785 --> 00:06:27,719
The people of chester's mill
will be permitted

127
00:06:27,721 --> 00:06:30,856
To visit with their loved ones
on the outside.

128
00:06:30,858 --> 00:06:33,658
The location for this
is where the dome intersects

129
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:35,894
With the sixth street bridge.

130
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:38,997
For further updates,
stay tuned to wybs.

131
00:06:50,543 --> 00:06:51,943
We need to talk.

132
00:06:51,945 --> 00:06:53,445
No, I know.
You heard the news?

133
00:06:53,447 --> 00:06:54,846
The feds are

134
00:06:54,848 --> 00:06:57,549
Bussing in people who got
caught outside the dome.

135
00:06:57,551 --> 00:06:59,651
What?

136
00:06:59,653 --> 00:07:01,420
Yeah, they just started
coming in this morning.

137
00:07:01,422 --> 00:07:02,721
The press, too.

138
00:07:02,723 --> 00:07:05,090
Well, you're gonna need help
with crowd control.

139
00:07:05,092 --> 00:07:07,592
Linda's already talking about
bringing in some more deputies.

140
00:07:07,594 --> 00:07:09,861
Time for talk is over.

141
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:11,897
I'm authorizing you
to recruit auxiliary officers.

142
00:07:11,899 --> 00:07:13,698
Dad, I...
How about carter?

143
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:15,434
The fullback from your year?

144
00:07:17,671 --> 00:07:20,772
I should get some
supplies first from...

145
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:22,641
The old shelter.

146
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:25,710
When I tell you to
do something, junior,

147
00:07:25,712 --> 00:07:27,179
What do you do?

148
00:07:27,181 --> 00:07:28,914
Dad, I know...
Now!

149
00:07:39,158 --> 00:07:41,460
Shouldn't we get your moms?

150
00:07:41,462 --> 00:07:42,727
Why?

151
00:07:42,729 --> 00:07:44,596
It's not like any of
their phony l.A. Friends

152
00:07:44,598 --> 00:07:46,131
Are gonna make the trip.

153
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:48,667
Yeah, but you never made it
to where you were headed.

154
00:07:48,669 --> 00:07:50,902
Somebody out there's
probably worried.

155
00:07:50,904 --> 00:07:52,971
Who cares?

156
00:07:52,973 --> 00:07:54,806
I'm just excited
to meet your folks.

157
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:56,074
I can't wait to tell them
you're shacking up

158
00:07:56,076 --> 00:07:58,043
With an underage girl
and two lesbians.

159
00:08:06,252 --> 00:08:08,153
barbie?

160
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:14,493
I can use your help.

161
00:08:14,495 --> 00:08:17,562
We need to keep people
a safe distance from this thing.

162
00:08:17,564 --> 00:08:19,898
We don't want people's cameras
or cell phones blowing up

163
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:21,700
Like duke's pacemaker.

164
00:08:21,702 --> 00:08:25,170
Until we find out
what the hell the dome is,

165
00:08:25,172 --> 00:08:28,173
I don't want anyone on our side
touching it, no matter what.

166
00:08:28,175 --> 00:08:30,242
You got it.

167
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:46,258
Rusty.

168
00:09:01,807 --> 00:09:04,709
Is it true? They're really
letting us see our families?

169
00:09:04,711 --> 00:09:05,944
Yeah.
Really?

170
00:09:05,946 --> 00:09:08,213
Hey, did dodee pick up
any chatter about this?

171
00:09:08,215 --> 00:09:11,082
Uh, no. I've been listening
to her e.T.-Phone-home thing,

172
00:09:11,084 --> 00:09:12,884
But the military broadcasts
dropped out last night

173
00:09:12,886 --> 00:09:15,987
So all we've been getting
are random numbers and crap.

174
00:09:20,827 --> 00:09:22,227
Man:
Zone one is painted.

175
00:09:22,229 --> 00:09:25,096
Green for 1315.

176
00:09:25,098 --> 00:09:26,831
Zone one is painted.

177
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:27,832
Green for 1315.

178
00:09:27,834 --> 00:09:29,234
What does that mean?

179
00:09:29,236 --> 00:09:32,604
Getting visitors is
the first good news we've had...

180
00:09:32,606 --> 00:09:33,738
Since ever.

181
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:35,006
...Global audience awaits
any hint

182
00:09:35,008 --> 00:09:37,008
Of what's happened inside...

183
00:09:37,010 --> 00:09:38,276
Do you think
he'll show up today?

184
00:09:38,278 --> 00:09:39,711
Peter?

185
00:09:39,713 --> 00:09:40,879
Julia, I...
Phil.

186
00:09:40,881 --> 00:09:43,748
It's all right.

187
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,884
Barbie told me
what you guys were into.

188
00:09:45,886 --> 00:09:48,253
I know my husband left me

189
00:09:48,255 --> 00:09:50,789
Because he has
a gambling problem.

190
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:53,058
But that was before all this.

191
00:09:53,060 --> 00:09:55,794
He's got to show
his face today, doesn't he?

192
00:09:55,796 --> 00:09:57,162
This is jeff glor
at chester's mill.

193
00:09:57,164 --> 00:09:59,197
It's been six days
yeah, I th...

194
00:09:59,199 --> 00:10:01,900
Since the invisible barrier
arrived over chester's mill.

195
00:10:01,902 --> 00:10:03,368
That doesn't sound
like another army guy.

196
00:10:03,370 --> 00:10:05,270
Ever since the military
evacuated surrounding towns

197
00:10:05,272 --> 00:10:07,939
And established
a ten-mile perimeter

198
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:10,342
Around what's being called
"the dome,"

199
00:10:10,344 --> 00:10:13,712
The world has been waiting
for news from inside.

200
00:10:13,714 --> 00:10:16,147
Last night,
the government relented,

201
00:10:16,149 --> 00:10:18,049
Allowing select members
of the press to document

202
00:10:18,051 --> 00:10:19,784
These emotional reunions.

203
00:10:19,786 --> 00:10:20,919
Man:
Ladies and gentlemen,

204
00:10:20,921 --> 00:10:22,220
As you approach the dome,

205
00:10:22,222 --> 00:10:25,757
Make sure if you have
a tablet in your hand

206
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:27,859
That you do not touch the dome.

207
00:10:33,766 --> 00:10:36,701
And look, we're famous.

208
00:10:36,703 --> 00:10:39,004
They want to make
a reality show out of us.

209
00:10:41,974 --> 00:10:42,974
I-I know...

210
00:10:46,846 --> 00:10:48,013
Norrie:
Who are you looking for?

211
00:10:48,015 --> 00:10:50,181
I'm looking for angie.

212
00:10:50,183 --> 00:10:51,282
You said your
sister's a flake.

213
00:10:51,284 --> 00:10:53,318
Yeah, she is, but...

214
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,186
She'd definitely
come to this.

215
00:10:58,090 --> 00:10:59,991
The hell?

216
00:10:59,993 --> 00:11:01,660
Nore?

217
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:15,974
No.

218
00:11:15,976 --> 00:11:18,176
My mom said I came
from an anonymous donor.

219
00:11:34,827 --> 00:11:36,227
Joe:
That's your mom.

220
00:11:40,099 --> 00:11:41,966
Sinners!

221
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:44,936
Sinners!

222
00:11:44,938 --> 00:11:47,305
Over and over,

223
00:11:47,307 --> 00:11:49,908
The lord has spoken one word

224
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:52,377
In my ear: Moab.

225
00:11:52,379 --> 00:11:54,112
Why?

226
00:11:54,114 --> 00:11:57,048
Because we
are moab.

227
00:11:58,418 --> 00:11:59,918
Moab!
Okay, thank you, reverend.

228
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,820
Thank you for those
inspiring words.

229
00:12:01,822 --> 00:12:03,722
Enjoy your loved ones.

230
00:12:04,757 --> 00:12:06,057
So help me god,

231
00:12:06,059 --> 00:12:07,726
If you ruin this day
for these people, I'm gonna...

232
00:12:07,728 --> 00:12:08,993
What, beat me to a pulp?

233
00:12:08,995 --> 00:12:10,228
In front of the congregation?

234
00:12:11,431 --> 00:12:14,733
I'm not scared of you
anymore, jim rennie.

235
00:12:14,735 --> 00:12:16,501
All I fear

236
00:12:16,503 --> 00:12:18,069
Is the wrath
of my lord.

237
00:12:18,071 --> 00:12:20,338
And the only way we're
gonna be spared his fury

238
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:22,173
Is if we confess our sins.

239
00:12:22,175 --> 00:12:23,408
Sins.
Hmm.

240
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:26,878
: We helped drug
dealers make their poison.

241
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,446
We never let 'em sell it here.

242
00:12:28,448 --> 00:12:30,348
It's not my fault
you dipped into their supply.

243
00:12:30,350 --> 00:12:32,951
All you ever think about is
fattening your own coffers.

244
00:12:32,953 --> 00:12:36,154
Damn it, lester,
you listen...
No, you listen to me!

245
00:12:36,156 --> 00:12:38,890
You may have fooled
some of these people

246
00:12:38,892 --> 00:12:41,326
Into thinking
you're some kind of leader.

247
00:12:41,328 --> 00:12:45,363
But nobody's going to
follow you anywhere, ever,

248
00:12:45,365 --> 00:12:47,432
When they hear just
exactly who you are.

249
00:12:51,337 --> 00:12:52,937
What do you want, reverend?

250
00:12:52,939 --> 00:12:55,240
For you admit your
sins before god,

251
00:12:55,242 --> 00:12:59,444
And every man and woman
in chester's mill.

252
00:12:59,446 --> 00:13:01,546
You have one day...

253
00:13:01,548 --> 00:13:04,082
One day to come clean...

254
00:13:06,085 --> 00:13:08,186
...Or I do it for you.

255
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:18,196
Glor:
It's the final hour
of the government's

256
00:13:18,198 --> 00:13:19,464
First visitors' day,
as the last of...

257
00:13:24,437 --> 00:13:26,037
Hey.

258
00:13:26,039 --> 00:13:27,539
That's my sister.

259
00:13:34,914 --> 00:13:36,181
Linda.

260
00:13:36,183 --> 00:13:38,116
Hey.

261
00:13:38,118 --> 00:13:39,484
Any sign of your husband?

262
00:13:39,486 --> 00:13:41,119
Not yet.

263
00:13:41,121 --> 00:13:43,121
What about you?
Did you find your fiancé?

264
00:13:43,123 --> 00:13:45,957
Yeah.

265
00:13:45,959 --> 00:13:47,425
Everything all right?

266
00:13:49,295 --> 00:13:51,830
I just... Couldn't bring
myself to tell him.

267
00:13:51,832 --> 00:13:53,364
About what?

268
00:13:56,435 --> 00:13:58,503
His brother.

269
00:14:00,906 --> 00:14:03,842
Linda, freddy's death
was an accident.

270
00:14:03,844 --> 00:14:06,611
He got shot on my watch.

271
00:14:06,613 --> 00:14:08,880
It's my responsibility
to tell rusty.

272
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:12,584
I just...

273
00:14:12,586 --> 00:14:14,319
I just don't know how.

274
00:14:15,287 --> 00:14:19,023
Yeah... You do.

275
00:14:24,430 --> 00:14:26,631
Carolyn:
Oh. Norrie?

276
00:14:26,633 --> 00:14:28,032
Norrie.

277
00:14:28,034 --> 00:14:30,501
Where the hell
have you been?

278
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:36,007
Michael?

279
00:14:36,009 --> 00:14:37,275
So it's true,

280
00:14:37,277 --> 00:14:39,244
This guy's my dad?

281
00:14:39,246 --> 00:14:41,279
Norrie, it's
complicated.

282
00:14:41,281 --> 00:14:45,016
No. You told me
the records were sealed.

283
00:14:45,018 --> 00:14:47,418
That we couldn't even
look for him.

284
00:14:47,420 --> 00:14:49,287
And all these years,
you've been lying to me.

285
00:14:49,289 --> 00:14:51,923
How dare you?

286
00:14:51,925 --> 00:14:54,158
You have never been anything
to this girl!

287
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:56,394
But the second that
cameras show up,

288
00:14:56,396 --> 00:14:57,662
You decide

289
00:14:57,664 --> 00:14:59,397
You suddenly have a daughter?
Alice...

290
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:01,165
Take it easy.
I hate you.

291
00:15:01,167 --> 00:15:03,401
I hate you all so much.

292
00:15:03,403 --> 00:15:06,905
Norrie!
Let's...

293
00:15:06,907 --> 00:15:08,406
Julia:
Barbie.

294
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:19,284
Have you seen him?

295
00:15:19,286 --> 00:15:21,352
Peter.

296
00:15:21,354 --> 00:15:23,054
I know that nothing
that I'm gonna say

297
00:15:23,056 --> 00:15:25,123
Is gonna make up for
the fact that I...

298
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:27,025
That I should have told
you the truth sooner.

299
00:15:27,027 --> 00:15:28,026
You're right.

300
00:15:28,028 --> 00:15:29,260
But I don't blame you

301
00:15:29,262 --> 00:15:31,095
For my husband's
bad decisions.

302
00:15:31,097 --> 00:15:33,698
And if you really want
to make it up to me,

303
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:36,334
Just keep an eye
out for him.

304
00:15:44,343 --> 00:15:46,044
Excuse me. Sorry.

305
00:15:46,046 --> 00:15:47,578
Mary.

306
00:16:12,038 --> 00:16:15,974
Julia,
what's the matter?

307
00:16:15,976 --> 00:16:17,375
That was my
sister-in-law.

308
00:16:18,344 --> 00:16:20,445
What did she say?

309
00:16:20,447 --> 00:16:22,080
She showed me a letter

310
00:16:22,082 --> 00:16:24,449
That she got
from my husband.

311
00:16:24,451 --> 00:16:27,552
It said, "I know
this is confusing,

312
00:16:27,554 --> 00:16:29,520
"but all I can
say is sorry.

313
00:16:31,457 --> 00:16:34,359
Tell julia she
deserves better."

314
00:16:38,397 --> 00:16:39,530
Guy didn't even
have the balls

315
00:16:39,532 --> 00:16:40,765
To send his own
dear john letter.

316
00:16:54,079 --> 00:16:56,748
Mrs. Grinnell:
Oh, my god,
I can't believe it.

317
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:59,484
I...

318
00:16:59,486 --> 00:17:01,252
Oh...

319
00:17:01,254 --> 00:17:03,154
Oh, I.... I...

320
00:17:03,156 --> 00:17:04,522
Ma'am.

321
00:17:04,524 --> 00:17:05,656
They don't want anyone
touching this thing, okay?

322
00:17:05,658 --> 00:17:09,694
I haven't spoken to him
in almost ten years,

323
00:17:09,696 --> 00:17:11,396
But here he is.
I'm sure.
Yeah.

324
00:17:11,398 --> 00:17:13,331
This thing brought him
back to me.
No, I-I...

325
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:14,565
I understand.

326
00:17:14,567 --> 00:17:16,067
Hey!

327
00:17:16,069 --> 00:17:17,502
Leave her be.

328
00:17:17,504 --> 00:17:18,703
You gotta be kidding me.

329
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:20,038
Somebody made <i>you</i> a cop?

330
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:22,106
We'll take it from here.

331
00:17:41,460 --> 00:17:44,228
It's about your brother.

332
00:17:56,475 --> 00:17:59,210
No.

333
00:17:59,212 --> 00:18:00,711
I'm so sorry.

334
00:18:00,713 --> 00:18:03,347
I'm so sorry.

335
00:18:10,489 --> 00:18:11,722
Joe:
Norrie, wait!

336
00:18:11,724 --> 00:18:13,758
I don't want
to talk about it.

337
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:15,226
Well, what did
your dad say?

338
00:18:15,228 --> 00:18:17,328
He's not my dad!

339
00:18:17,330 --> 00:18:20,198
He's just some creep
who wants to be on tv.

340
00:18:23,669 --> 00:18:26,370
Look, I'm sorry.

341
00:18:26,372 --> 00:18:27,772
I just always imagined

342
00:18:27,774 --> 00:18:31,676
That maybe I'd get to meet
a part of my past, and...

343
00:18:31,678 --> 00:18:34,779
Never really pictured it
going quite like that.

344
00:18:38,217 --> 00:18:39,484
Ben:
Yo, mcalister!

345
00:18:39,486 --> 00:18:41,719
Ben, were you
at visitors' day?

346
00:18:41,721 --> 00:18:43,855
Pretty much everyone
I actually like

347
00:18:43,857 --> 00:18:45,690
Is stuck in here
with us, so...

348
00:18:45,692 --> 00:18:47,458
I just talked to
random strangers.

349
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:48,893
About what?

350
00:18:48,895 --> 00:18:50,261
Did you hear china
threatened to attack us

351
00:18:50,263 --> 00:18:51,329
After the dome showed up?

352
00:18:51,331 --> 00:18:52,330
Seriously?

353
00:18:52,332 --> 00:18:56,400
Thought we were testing some
kind of illegal superweapon,

354
00:18:56,402 --> 00:18:58,603
So the president had to
talk 'em off the ledge,

355
00:18:58,605 --> 00:19:00,571
Tell them we didn't
even build it.

356
00:19:00,573 --> 00:19:01,906
Great.

357
00:19:01,908 --> 00:19:05,409
Sounds like the grown-ups
have it all under control.

358
00:19:12,351 --> 00:19:14,919
Man:
Bye, so long. We love you.

359
00:19:14,921 --> 00:19:17,221
Soldier:
Ma'am, it's time to go.

360
00:19:29,668 --> 00:19:31,569
Excuse me.
Can you read lips

361
00:19:31,571 --> 00:19:32,670
As well as you do
sign language?

362
00:19:32,672 --> 00:19:33,738
Maybe.

363
00:19:33,740 --> 00:19:34,839
What's in it for me?

364
00:19:34,841 --> 00:19:36,841
Answers.

365
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:56,327
Dodee:
You know this guy?

366
00:19:56,329 --> 00:19:58,429
No, but my old unit
is kind of infamous.

367
00:19:58,431 --> 00:19:59,463
Do me a favor.

368
00:19:59,465 --> 00:20:00,598
Just tell me what
this guy's saying.

369
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,533
It's an honor to meet

370
00:20:02,535 --> 00:20:03,834
One of the jackrabbits, sir.

371
00:20:03,836 --> 00:20:05,736
How are things
in there?

372
00:20:05,738 --> 00:20:09,207
Uh, forget about us.

373
00:20:09,209 --> 00:20:12,843
What's... Happening...

374
00:20:12,845 --> 00:20:14,478
Out... There?

375
00:20:22,321 --> 00:20:25,556
Dodee:
Something big is going down.

376
00:20:25,558 --> 00:20:27,992
They told us
to pull out after this.

377
00:20:27,994 --> 00:20:29,360
All of us.

378
00:20:30,863 --> 00:20:32,763
No clue.

379
00:20:32,765 --> 00:20:34,599
But they said once we leave...

380
00:20:34,601 --> 00:20:36,701
But they said
once we leave...

381
00:20:36,703 --> 00:20:38,569
Don't plan on coming back.

382
00:20:41,607 --> 00:20:43,641
Sorry, sir. We're on the move.

383
00:20:50,983 --> 00:20:53,951
Dodee:
Last night.

384
00:20:53,953 --> 00:20:55,886
After the butterflies
showed up.

385
00:20:55,888 --> 00:20:57,355
Butterflies?

386
00:20:58,457 --> 00:21:00,391
Yeah, there was
a whole swarm of 'em.

387
00:21:00,393 --> 00:21:01,926
It covered part of the dome.

388
00:21:01,928 --> 00:21:02,927
Huh.

389
00:21:02,929 --> 00:21:04,428
What?

390
00:21:04,430 --> 00:21:06,664
A lot of insects use
magnetic fields to navigate.

391
00:21:06,666 --> 00:21:08,466
If the dome is
altering them, then...

392
00:21:08,468 --> 00:21:10,268
There is no way in hell

393
00:21:10,270 --> 00:21:12,637
The government would
stand for that.

394
00:21:12,639 --> 00:21:14,639
They're not about to
let this thing mess

395
00:21:14,641 --> 00:21:15,773
With the outside world.

396
00:21:15,775 --> 00:21:17,308
Well, what does that mean?

397
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:22,580
Moab.

398
00:21:22,582 --> 00:21:23,748
Come again?

399
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:26,517
What your reverend
was ranting about.

400
00:21:26,519 --> 00:21:28,419
His hearing aid must have
intercepted a transmission

401
00:21:28,421 --> 00:21:30,821
Like the ones
that you're picking up
at the station station.

402
00:21:30,823 --> 00:21:33,658
But why would the army be
telling bible stories?

403
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:35,826
Moab is not a city,
it's an acronym:

404
00:21:35,828 --> 00:21:37,762
Moab-- "mother of all bombs."

405
00:21:37,764 --> 00:21:39,063
That's what we call

406
00:21:39,065 --> 00:21:41,032
The largest nonnuclear missile
in our arsenal.

407
00:21:41,034 --> 00:21:43,968
You think they're
gonna launch that
thing at the dome?

408
00:21:43,970 --> 00:21:45,670
Would it work?

409
00:21:45,672 --> 00:21:46,904
Yeah.

410
00:21:46,906 --> 00:21:49,073
Then why don't you look happy?

411
00:21:49,075 --> 00:21:51,709
Because it'll also kill
everybody inside.

412
00:21:51,711 --> 00:21:53,611
What?!
Dodee,

413
00:21:53,613 --> 00:21:57,448
Visitors' day was not about
saying hello to your families.

414
00:21:57,450 --> 00:21:59,483
It was about saying good-bye.

415
00:22:16,868 --> 00:22:18,636
How'd it go with rusty?

416
00:22:18,638 --> 00:22:21,639
As well as it could, I guess.

417
00:22:21,641 --> 00:22:23,574
He left without even
saying good-bye.

418
00:22:23,576 --> 00:22:26,010
Still, I'm glad
I told him.

419
00:22:26,012 --> 00:22:27,812
So thank you.

420
00:22:27,814 --> 00:22:29,613
Councilman rennie!

421
00:22:29,615 --> 00:22:31,916
We're dead.
It's coming down.

422
00:22:31,918 --> 00:22:34,518
What-what-what are
you talking about?

423
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:37,355
The army is gonna blow up
the dome,

424
00:22:37,357 --> 00:22:39,457
Even if that means
blowing us up with it.

425
00:22:39,459 --> 00:22:43,027
I just got the word from
a soldier on the other side.

426
00:22:43,029 --> 00:22:46,130
They're gonna launch a
thermobaric missile right at us.

427
00:22:46,132 --> 00:22:47,898
Good lord! Any idea when?

428
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:52,370
From outside the dome, but,
no, I-I don't have a timetable.

429
00:22:52,372 --> 00:22:53,504
I think I do.

430
00:22:53,506 --> 00:22:54,672
At the radio station
this morning,

431
00:22:54,674 --> 00:22:55,773
Phil and I heard something:

432
00:22:55,775 --> 00:22:59,510
"zone one is painted green
for 1315."

433
00:22:59,512 --> 00:23:01,445
Yeah. "painted" means
that a target's been approved.

434
00:23:01,447 --> 00:23:03,013
"zone one" was written
on all their trucks,

435
00:23:03,015 --> 00:23:04,415
So it's gotta be
chester's mill.

436
00:23:04,417 --> 00:23:06,450
And 1315?
Military time.

437
00:23:06,452 --> 00:23:08,152
That's 1:15 this afternoon.

438
00:23:08,154 --> 00:23:10,955
That's less than
three hours.
Dodee:
So that's it?

439
00:23:10,957 --> 00:23:12,923
We're all just gonna die?
Linda:
No, no.

440
00:23:12,925 --> 00:23:14,825
We get everybody to a shelter.

441
00:23:14,827 --> 00:23:15,893
Where?

442
00:23:15,895 --> 00:23:17,161
The old cement factory.

443
00:23:17,163 --> 00:23:18,896
Some of those tunnels
run pretty deep.

444
00:23:18,898 --> 00:23:20,598
Linda:
So, what? We just relocate
the entire town?

445
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:22,800
What about the sick,
the elderly?
I'll dispatch

446
00:23:22,802 --> 00:23:24,468
A fleet from the car lot
to help with transport.

447
00:23:24,470 --> 00:23:25,836
Let's just do it
the best we can.

448
00:23:25,838 --> 00:23:27,405
All right. Hurry.

449
00:23:27,407 --> 00:23:29,640
I'm so sorry, sweetie.
I still haven't seen angie.

450
00:23:29,642 --> 00:23:31,175
Maybe she's volunteering
at the clinic.

451
00:23:31,177 --> 00:23:32,676
We just checked there.

452
00:23:32,678 --> 00:23:34,845
They haven't seen angie
since the first dome day.

453
00:23:34,847 --> 00:23:38,149
This is julia shumway
with an emergency broadcast.

454
00:23:38,151 --> 00:23:40,084
I know this news
might be difficult

455
00:23:40,086 --> 00:23:42,052
For many of you to accept,

456
00:23:42,054 --> 00:23:44,622
But I give you my word
that it is the truth.

457
00:23:44,624 --> 00:23:50,060
At 1:15 today the military plans
to launch a powerful missile

458
00:23:50,062 --> 00:23:53,431
At our town in the hopes
of destroying the dome.

459
00:23:53,433 --> 00:23:56,934
Because we don't know what will
happen when the dome collapses,

460
00:23:56,936 --> 00:23:59,437
It is imperative
that we take shelter.

461
00:23:59,439 --> 00:24:04,508
For your safety, all residents
of chester's mill must go

462
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:07,211
To sanders cement works
immediately.

463
00:24:07,213 --> 00:24:12,216
Please do everything you can
to help spread the word.

464
00:24:12,218 --> 00:24:15,152
This is not a drill.

465
00:24:22,561 --> 00:24:24,228
Mr. Rennie...

466
00:24:29,836 --> 00:24:32,870
Oh!

467
00:24:39,211 --> 00:24:43,747
I can't apologize enough
for what junior did to you.

468
00:24:43,749 --> 00:24:48,252
He was a good boy.

469
00:24:48,254 --> 00:24:50,721
I don't know where I lost him.

470
00:24:52,591 --> 00:24:54,091
Anyway, um,

471
00:24:54,093 --> 00:24:56,961
You can go now.

472
00:25:01,199 --> 00:25:03,267
Why are you doing this?

473
00:25:04,769 --> 00:25:07,071
Well, if we're all gonna
die today...

474
00:25:09,774 --> 00:25:12,576
...You might as well die
a free woman.

475
00:25:34,132 --> 00:25:36,066
♪

476
00:25:45,677 --> 00:25:47,678
Julia:
We're working on the lights,
sweetheart, okay?

477
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:50,014
So it won't be dark
for too much longer.

478
00:25:50,016 --> 00:25:53,918
And we'll get you a cot
as soon as we can.

479
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:55,920
You almost finished
battening down the hatches ?

480
00:25:55,922 --> 00:25:59,890
Barbie:
Yeah.

481
00:25:59,892 --> 00:26:01,125
For what it's worth.

482
00:26:02,827 --> 00:26:05,162
Julia, when that missile breaks
through here...

483
00:26:05,164 --> 00:26:06,864
I know.

484
00:26:10,268 --> 00:26:13,571
Hey. Dodee told me
how you got the story.

485
00:26:13,573 --> 00:26:15,773
Said the soldier
started talking

486
00:26:15,775 --> 00:26:17,975
When you showed him
some sort of a coin?

487
00:26:20,178 --> 00:26:23,581
I-I'm not asking
on the record.

488
00:26:27,586 --> 00:26:29,987
That guy that we met,
he probably only talked to us

489
00:26:29,989 --> 00:26:32,089
'cause he thinks that I'm...

490
00:26:32,091 --> 00:26:34,592
Some kind of hero.

491
00:26:34,594 --> 00:26:36,226
You're not?

492
00:26:38,229 --> 00:26:40,064
One of my deployments in iraq,

493
00:26:40,066 --> 00:26:43,267
Um... My unit helped rescue

494
00:26:43,269 --> 00:26:46,704
A captured soldier
from insurgents

495
00:26:46,706 --> 00:26:49,673
After her company had been
killed by small arms fire.

496
00:26:49,675 --> 00:26:51,809
God.

497
00:26:53,645 --> 00:26:56,814
The insurgents captured
that soldier.

498
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:01,085
They didn't kill her company.

499
00:27:04,856 --> 00:27:06,857
We did.

500
00:27:06,859 --> 00:27:08,058
We were on patrol.

501
00:27:08,060 --> 00:27:12,296
All of a sudden,
someone starts shooting at us,

502
00:27:12,298 --> 00:27:17,668
And it's not until the dust
clears we realize...

503
00:27:17,670 --> 00:27:20,337
We'd just shot up our own side.

504
00:27:22,741 --> 00:27:26,877
Killed every soldier except the
one that the enemy hauled off.

505
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:32,149
Maybe this is how
I deserve to go.

506
00:27:34,653 --> 00:27:36,920
More friendly fire.

507
00:27:47,198 --> 00:27:49,233
Junior!

508
00:27:50,935 --> 00:27:54,405
Dad... What are you doing here?

509
00:27:54,407 --> 00:27:55,939
You first.

510
00:27:55,941 --> 00:27:59,176
I-I-I heard about the missile.

511
00:27:59,178 --> 00:28:02,813
I figured maybe we go take cover
in the old bomb shelter.

512
00:28:03,782 --> 00:28:05,683
I know, junior.

513
00:28:05,685 --> 00:28:08,185
What are you talking about?

514
00:28:08,187 --> 00:28:10,187
About angie.

515
00:28:11,156 --> 00:28:13,891
I let her go.

516
00:28:14,826 --> 00:28:16,126
You did what?

517
00:28:16,128 --> 00:28:18,862
What the hell were you thinking?

518
00:28:18,864 --> 00:28:21,331
I mean...

519
00:28:21,333 --> 00:28:23,967
Junior, that doesn't matter
anymore, junior.

520
00:28:23,969 --> 00:28:26,203
Junior, we just need to get down
to that factory.

521
00:28:26,205 --> 00:28:27,705
The town needs us, junior.

522
00:28:27,707 --> 00:28:28,839
Junior!

523
00:28:28,841 --> 00:28:30,340
Junior!

524
00:28:38,116 --> 00:28:41,151
Phil, it is way past go-time!
Hurry it up!

525
00:28:41,153 --> 00:28:42,753
Hold on. I'm setting up
a playlist

526
00:28:42,755 --> 00:28:43,987
To broadcast right after
we leave.

527
00:28:43,989 --> 00:28:46,390
I just have
to play one last song

528
00:28:46,392 --> 00:28:47,991
Before this thing hits.
This is probably

529
00:28:47,993 --> 00:28:49,893
The very last thing anyone's
ever gonna hear, okay?

530
00:28:49,895 --> 00:28:51,462
But I thought we're gonna
be safe in those tunnels.

531
00:28:51,464 --> 00:28:55,132
From weapons
of mass destruction?

532
00:28:55,134 --> 00:28:57,935
So-so you think this is
gonna be the end?

533
00:29:00,138 --> 00:29:03,207
13 minutes, we find out.

534
00:29:05,043 --> 00:29:07,344
Hello?!

535
00:29:07,346 --> 00:29:09,146
Joe?!

536
00:29:09,148 --> 00:29:12,015
Joe? Joe?!

537
00:29:15,954 --> 00:29:17,354
Where the hell is everybody?!

538
00:29:17,356 --> 00:29:19,490
Joe!

539
00:29:25,097 --> 00:29:28,499
I knew you'd
come here.

540
00:29:31,970 --> 00:29:34,271
We're not finished yet.

541
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:48,886
Just find a place

542
00:29:48,888 --> 00:29:50,521
Somewhere over
there, okay?

543
00:29:50,523 --> 00:29:52,055
Hey. How's everything
out there?

544
00:29:52,057 --> 00:29:53,524
Under control.

545
00:29:53,526 --> 00:29:56,026
I think I got the last
of the holdouts.

546
00:29:56,028 --> 00:29:57,194
Where's junior?

547
00:29:57,196 --> 00:29:59,897
Just, uh...

548
00:29:59,899 --> 00:30:01,398
Tying up a few loose ends.

549
00:30:03,501 --> 00:30:06,270
Make sure your new guys
keep the peace in here.

550
00:30:07,806 --> 00:30:09,072
Where are you going?

551
00:30:09,074 --> 00:30:11,208
Tying up a few
loose ends.

552
00:30:21,019 --> 00:30:22,152
Phil.

553
00:30:24,489 --> 00:30:25,889
Beethoven?

554
00:30:25,891 --> 00:30:28,492
Keeps the folks mellow.

555
00:30:38,036 --> 00:30:40,103
Got something for you.

556
00:30:43,541 --> 00:30:46,210
What are you doing?

557
00:30:46,212 --> 00:30:48,045
It's your watch.

558
00:30:48,047 --> 00:30:50,914
It's my grandfather's watch.

559
00:30:50,916 --> 00:30:52,149
Yeah, I figured
it probably had

560
00:30:52,151 --> 00:30:53,584
Some sentimental value.

561
00:30:54,519 --> 00:30:57,020
I bet on the browns, barbie.

562
00:30:57,022 --> 00:30:59,957
That's losing,
fair and square.

563
00:30:59,959 --> 00:31:02,059
Well, maybe I'm getting
out of that line of work.

564
00:31:02,994 --> 00:31:05,362
Good luck, phil.

565
00:31:14,873 --> 00:31:17,407
I got you this
in the fourth grade, remember?

566
00:31:17,409 --> 00:31:18,876
When my parents

567
00:31:18,878 --> 00:31:20,244
Took me to new york?

568
00:31:20,246 --> 00:31:21,378
Junior...

569
00:31:21,380 --> 00:31:24,548
What's happening?

570
00:31:38,029 --> 00:31:41,164
Julia:
This is a prerecorded
emergency broadcast.

571
00:31:41,166 --> 00:31:42,432
At 1:15 p.M. Today,

572
00:31:42,434 --> 00:31:46,136
The military plans to launch
a powerful missile

573
00:31:46,138 --> 00:31:49,006
At our town, in the hopes of
destroying the dome.

574
00:31:49,008 --> 00:31:50,574
What does that mean?

575
00:31:52,210 --> 00:31:53,477
We're all gonna die.

576
00:31:53,479 --> 00:31:54,912
Junior, you don't...

577
00:31:54,914 --> 00:31:56,046
Yes, I do.

578
00:31:56,048 --> 00:31:58,482
From the very beginning.

579
00:32:02,053 --> 00:32:04,087
I'm so sorry, ange.

580
00:32:07,458 --> 00:32:10,594
All I wanted to do was
to help you to get better.

581
00:32:28,646 --> 00:32:29,713
Oh...

582
00:32:51,970 --> 00:32:53,403
Last call?

583
00:32:57,977 --> 00:33:00,711
An editor gave me this bottle
after my first byline.

584
00:33:02,180 --> 00:33:04,715
Been looking for a good excuse
to drink it ever since.

585
00:33:07,453 --> 00:33:08,752
It worth the wait?

586
00:33:08,754 --> 00:33:10,587
It's horrible.

587
00:33:10,589 --> 00:33:12,656
My bosses always hate me.

588
00:33:15,994 --> 00:33:18,495
You know,
I still miss chicago, but...

589
00:33:18,497 --> 00:33:21,231
Peter always said
I'd grow to love this place.

590
00:33:23,234 --> 00:33:24,267
Where do you
think he is now?

591
00:33:24,269 --> 00:33:26,403
Some flophouse in vegas?

592
00:33:26,405 --> 00:33:28,005
Oh, julia...

593
00:33:28,007 --> 00:33:30,107
Well, I made my peace with it.

594
00:33:30,109 --> 00:33:33,243
Besides, maybe he was right.

595
00:33:33,245 --> 00:33:35,412
You know, I didn't
understand this place

596
00:33:35,414 --> 00:33:37,214
Before the dome came down.

597
00:33:37,216 --> 00:33:42,152
But now, after everything
we've been through...

598
00:33:42,154 --> 00:33:44,321
I'm glad I got to
be a part of it.

599
00:33:49,427 --> 00:33:51,294
Julia, there's something
that you need to hear.

600
00:33:51,296 --> 00:33:54,231
You don't understand...
Alice:
Help! Please!

601
00:33:54,233 --> 00:33:56,299
We need help!
Has anyone seen
our daughter?

602
00:33:56,301 --> 00:33:57,567
Alice:
Our daughter, norrie.
She's tall,

603
00:33:57,569 --> 00:33:59,369
She's got red hair.
Has anyone seen her?

604
00:33:59,371 --> 00:34:00,437
Alice?

605
00:34:00,439 --> 00:34:01,638
Yes.

606
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:02,773
I saw your daughter
at visitors' day.

607
00:34:02,775 --> 00:34:07,377
And we-we haven't seen her,
or her friend joe, since.

608
00:34:07,379 --> 00:34:08,545
I-I'm going
back out there.

609
00:34:08,547 --> 00:34:14,184
Our girl is still
out there.
I'm sorry, you're
not going to be able

610
00:34:14,186 --> 00:34:16,086
To leave right now.
Carolyn: No, no, no...

611
00:34:16,088 --> 00:34:17,654
Whoa, whoa. Where...
Where you going?

612
00:34:17,656 --> 00:34:19,322
When I followed junior
down here a few days ago,

613
00:34:19,324 --> 00:34:20,323
We found another way out.

614
00:34:20,325 --> 00:34:21,525
We gotta find those kids.

615
00:34:24,095 --> 00:34:25,462
Joe:
Angie!

616
00:34:25,464 --> 00:34:26,563
Angie!

617
00:34:26,565 --> 00:34:27,798
Angie!

618
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:30,067
Angie!
Ange!

619
00:34:34,539 --> 00:34:36,106
You should go back
to the shelter.

620
00:34:36,108 --> 00:34:37,641
No, I want
to stay with you.

621
00:34:37,643 --> 00:34:39,743
You should be
with your moms.

622
00:34:39,745 --> 00:34:41,411
They're your family.

623
00:34:41,413 --> 00:34:43,480
But you're my friend.

624
00:34:47,351 --> 00:34:49,519
All right.
Come on.

625
00:34:56,094 --> 00:35:02,666
♪ why does the sun
go on shining? ♪

626
00:35:02,668 --> 00:35:09,239
♪ why does the sea
rush to shore? ♪

627
00:35:09,241 --> 00:35:11,875
♪ don't they know
you played this?

628
00:35:11,877 --> 00:35:15,112
♪ it's the end of the world?
Skeeter davis.

629
00:35:15,114 --> 00:35:16,379
She is a legend.

630
00:35:16,381 --> 00:35:21,151
♪ 'cause you don't
love me anymore ♪

631
00:35:23,254 --> 00:35:29,893
♪ why do the birds
go on singing? ♪

632
00:35:29,895 --> 00:35:35,599
♪ why do the stars glow above?

633
00:35:37,368 --> 00:35:39,669
♪ don't they know

634
00:35:39,671 --> 00:35:43,406
♪ it's the end of the world?

635
00:35:43,408 --> 00:35:48,879
♪ it ended
when I lost your love ♪

636
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:53,216
♪ I wake up in the morning

637
00:35:53,218 --> 00:35:57,454
♪ and I wonder...

638
00:35:57,456 --> 00:35:59,189
Can I say
something, phil?

639
00:35:59,191 --> 00:36:02,659
Anything in
the whole world.

640
00:36:02,661 --> 00:36:04,261
I hate you.

641
00:36:04,263 --> 00:36:05,395
Yeah?

642
00:36:05,397 --> 00:36:06,563
Mm-hmm.

643
00:36:06,565 --> 00:36:08,298
I hate you, too.

644
00:36:08,300 --> 00:36:10,834
♪ no, I can't understand

645
00:36:10,836 --> 00:36:17,307
♪ how life goes on
the way it does ♪

646
00:36:17,309 --> 00:36:20,577
♪ why does my heart

647
00:36:20,579 --> 00:36:24,714
♪ go on beating?

648
00:36:24,716 --> 00:36:31,321
♪ why do these eyes
of mine cry? ♪

649
00:36:31,323 --> 00:36:34,791
♪ don't they know

650
00:36:34,793 --> 00:36:38,195
♪ it's the end of the world?

651
00:36:38,197 --> 00:36:41,331
♪ 'cause you don't love me...

652
00:36:44,702 --> 00:36:46,870
Joe!

653
00:36:46,872 --> 00:36:48,205
W-we're too late.

654
00:36:57,616 --> 00:36:59,683
What are we
gonna do?

655
00:37:23,375 --> 00:37:26,376
All right, everybody,
stay put and remain calm.

656
00:37:26,378 --> 00:37:28,578
I'm gonna get some answers.

657
00:37:42,860 --> 00:37:43,860
How...

658
00:37:43,862 --> 00:37:45,629
W-when we touched,

659
00:37:45,631 --> 00:37:47,530
We didn't have
the seizures.

660
00:37:47,532 --> 00:37:49,899
More importantly, we didn't die.

661
00:37:57,809 --> 00:38:00,677
Big jim:
Linda. Linda, come in.

662
00:38:00,679 --> 00:38:02,712
What's the word, jim?

663
00:38:02,714 --> 00:38:04,014
I'm not sure yet,

664
00:38:04,016 --> 00:38:06,449
But everyone's okay.

665
00:38:26,871 --> 00:38:28,938
Oh, my god.

666
00:39:50,054 --> 00:39:52,622
He saved us.

667
00:39:52,624 --> 00:39:54,424
What the hell
are you doing here?

668
00:39:54,426 --> 00:39:57,894
Hell has got nothing
to do with it.

669
00:39:57,896 --> 00:40:00,697
God told me to
come out here.

670
00:40:00,699 --> 00:40:03,967
To see the moment of our
salvation for myself.

671
00:40:08,973 --> 00:40:10,573
Lester...
The good lord

672
00:40:10,575 --> 00:40:12,809
Saved chester's mill.

673
00:40:12,811 --> 00:40:14,477
Because I repented.

674
00:40:15,713 --> 00:40:17,046
And now it's
time for you

675
00:40:17,048 --> 00:40:18,648
To do the same.

676
00:40:18,650 --> 00:40:20,784
Jim, I know...

677
00:40:20,786 --> 00:40:22,819
You think this town
belongs to you.

678
00:40:22,821 --> 00:40:24,888
And maybe...
Maybe it used to.

679
00:40:24,890 --> 00:40:26,956
But today...

680
00:40:26,958 --> 00:40:29,025
Today's a new day.

681
00:40:30,594 --> 00:40:33,029
This dome has
only one master.

682
00:40:33,964 --> 00:40:36,666
And we are all
his servants.

683
00:40:39,937 --> 00:40:41,571
You know,
you're right, reverend.

684
00:40:41,573 --> 00:40:43,173
Today is a new day.

685
00:41:11,168 --> 00:41:13,236
♪
